111
00:08:31,745 --> 00:08:32,946
Gon: Ging.

112
00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:37,884
Ging: How long did it take you

113
00:08:37,918 --> 00:08:40,854
to get here
from the 500-meter Mark?

114
00:08:40,888 --> 00:08:44,959
gon: Uh,
probably about 20 minutes?

115
00:08:44,992 --> 00:08:48,629
Ging: Well, I guess that’s
not bad for your first time.

116
00:08:48,662 --> 00:08:50,030
Eat up.

117
00:08:52,065 --> 00:08:53,199
( Gon grunts )

118
00:08:59,506 --> 00:09:01,241
Whoa.

119
00:09:01,275 --> 00:09:03,577
Ging: Nice view, huh?

120
00:09:03,610 --> 00:09:06,680
When it’s overcast,
it’s like a sea of clouds.

121
00:09:06,713 --> 00:09:08,014
Gon: Wow!

122
00:09:08,048 --> 00:09:09,983
( Birds meowing )

123
00:09:11,051 --> 00:09:12,619
Gon: Hey, ging...

124
00:09:12,653 --> 00:09:13,921
Ging: Hmm?

125
00:09:13,954 --> 00:09:15,756
Gon: Can I ask you something?

126
00:09:15,789 --> 00:09:18,225
Ging: Sure. Don’t count
on an answer, though.

127
00:09:19,693 --> 00:09:22,196
Gon: What is it
that you want, really?

128
00:09:23,297 --> 00:09:24,632
Ging: Hmm.

129
00:09:27,568 --> 00:09:31,806
I want whatever
I don’t have, I guess.

130
00:09:33,774 --> 00:09:35,276
Gon: Whatever you don’t have?

131
00:09:35,309 --> 00:09:37,178
( Birds meowing )

132
00:09:42,816 --> 00:09:43,884
( Birds meowing )

133
00:09:47,888 --> 00:09:50,224
Ging: I think I wanted
to become a hunter

134
00:09:50,257 --> 00:09:54,228
because i--quiet!

135
00:09:54,261 --> 00:09:55,195
( Meowing stops )

136
00:09:58,999 --> 00:10:01,468
I wanted to become
a hunter, because,

137
00:10:01,502 --> 00:10:06,674
well, at the time, that is,
it was the most realistic way

138
00:10:06,707 --> 00:10:10,477
that I could get to a place
that I really wanted to see.

139
00:10:10,511 --> 00:10:11,779
♪

140
00:10:11,812 --> 00:10:14,048
The place i’m talking about
was being used

141
00:10:14,081 --> 00:10:16,550
as a royal family’s
burial ground.

142
00:10:17,851 --> 00:10:19,786
The only expeditions
into the area

143
00:10:19,820 --> 00:10:22,690
were privately funded
and sworn to secrecy.

144
00:10:22,723 --> 00:10:26,026
still, they never
brought back much research.

145
00:10:28,061 --> 00:10:31,598
in other words,
you couldn’t explore it at all.

146
00:10:33,167 --> 00:10:36,771
you won’t find anyone
willing to spend the resources,

147
00:10:36,803 --> 00:10:39,472
not when they won’t
get anything in return.

148
00:10:41,742 --> 00:10:44,845
But I still saw it
as my chance.

149
00:10:44,878 --> 00:10:47,581
If I could just become
a pro hunter,

150
00:10:47,614 --> 00:10:49,549
getting money
wouldn’t be a problem.

151
00:10:50,617 --> 00:10:52,285
I turned 15,

152
00:10:52,319 --> 00:10:55,022
and I set up a special
nonprofit corporation

153
00:10:55,055 --> 00:10:58,559
whose sole purpose was
to research and repair the tomb.

154
00:10:59,893 --> 00:11:03,096
before that,
right after getting my license,

155
00:11:03,130 --> 00:11:06,266
I spent two years studying
all the archaeology websites

156
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:08,636
and online blogs I could find.

157
00:11:10,971 --> 00:11:14,708
To create the nonprofit,
I needed about ten eccentrics.

158
00:11:14,741 --> 00:11:16,776
specifically,
I was looking for ones

159
00:11:16,810 --> 00:11:18,779
who didn’t need money or fame,

160
00:11:18,812 --> 00:11:21,048
but only wanted
to know the truth,

161
00:11:21,081 --> 00:11:24,985
and of course ones who could
be trusted to keep secrets.

162
00:11:27,688 --> 00:11:29,924
I’m always going
after everything I want

163
00:11:29,957 --> 00:11:32,993
in the moment, no matter what.

164
00:11:33,026 --> 00:11:35,262
I’m so focused that I
will completely stop caring

165
00:11:35,295 --> 00:11:37,964
about the object of my desire.

166
00:11:39,132 --> 00:11:40,233
Gon: Hmm.

167
00:11:42,336 --> 00:11:44,672
Ging: Still don’t get it?

168
00:11:44,705 --> 00:11:46,874
Well, guess i’ll
keep going, then.

169
00:11:46,907 --> 00:11:48,709
( Grunts )

170
00:11:50,911 --> 00:11:52,980
I recruited people online

171
00:11:53,013 --> 00:11:55,249
and made lots of friends
in meetings,

172
00:11:55,282 --> 00:11:57,684
but they were
all older than me,

173
00:11:57,718 --> 00:12:00,688
regular pencil pushers
and some students,

174
00:12:00,721 --> 00:12:02,823
a few freelancers.

175
00:12:04,391 --> 00:12:07,327
after I told them
about my background and my plan,

176
00:12:07,361 --> 00:12:11,599
they helped with all kinds of
tasks to create the nonprofit.

177
00:12:11,632 --> 00:12:14,902
they even gave donations
from what little money they had.

178
00:12:17,738 --> 00:12:19,206
When our dream was realized

179
00:12:19,239 --> 00:12:21,875
and we stepped inside
for the first time,

180
00:12:21,909 --> 00:12:24,712
I couldn’t hide
how happy I was,

181
00:12:24,745 --> 00:12:26,213
but what made me happiest

182
00:12:26,246 --> 00:12:29,683
wasn’t when I finally saw
the truth behind the tomb.

183
00:12:32,119 --> 00:12:36,290
No. It was when I looked
at my colleagues’s faces

184
00:12:36,323 --> 00:12:38,659
and we shook each other’s hands.

185
00:12:41,762 --> 00:12:43,697
♪

186
00:12:49,169 --> 00:12:52,339
they still work
for the nonprofit to this day,

187
00:12:52,372 --> 00:12:56,276
pro bono, providing me
with viable information.

188
00:12:57,744 --> 00:12:59,946
Compared to the people I met,

189
00:12:59,980 --> 00:13:04,351
the information I got
from the tomb was just a bonus.

190
00:13:04,384 --> 00:13:06,953
The most important thing,

191
00:13:06,987 --> 00:13:10,958
by a long shot, I already had.

192
00:13:10,991 --> 00:13:12,926
♪

193
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:15,896
( No audible dialogue )

194
00:13:26,740 --> 00:13:29,042
( Birds calling )

195
00:13:29,076 --> 00:13:30,411
Gon: And now?

196
00:13:30,444 --> 00:13:31,979
Ging: Huh?

197
00:13:32,012 --> 00:13:34,715
Gon: You know what you’re
gonna go after now?

198
00:13:34,748 --> 00:13:37,017
Ging: Like right now?

199
00:13:37,050 --> 00:13:39,219
that’ll take
a little time to explain.

200
00:13:40,821 --> 00:13:44,892
Tell me, gon, what is
this tree we just climbed?

201
00:13:44,925 --> 00:13:47,327
Gon: Huh? It’s the world tree.

202
00:13:47,361 --> 00:13:49,396
Ging: That’s right.

203
00:13:49,429 --> 00:13:51,798
and exactly how
did the people you met below

204
00:13:51,832 --> 00:13:53,200
describe the tree?

205
00:13:53,233 --> 00:13:55,836
Gon: It’s actually
the world’s largest tree,

206
00:13:55,869 --> 00:13:58,805
at 1,784 meters tall.

207
00:13:58,839 --> 00:14:00,774
Ging: Hmm.

208
00:14:00,807 --> 00:14:03,843
I guess technically
they aren’t wrong, but...

209
00:14:05,412 --> 00:14:08,248
The truth is this tree
is a young sapling,

210
00:14:08,282 --> 00:14:10,417
one that’s stopped growing.

211
00:14:10,450 --> 00:14:12,018
( Gon gasps )

212
00:14:12,052 --> 00:14:14,788
Ging: It didn’t get
enough nutrients,

213
00:14:14,821 --> 00:14:18,725
and it wound up a lot shorter
than it could have been.

214
00:14:18,759 --> 00:14:20,361
( Gon gasps )

215
00:14:26,099 --> 00:14:28,034
( Wind blowing )

216
00:14:31,872 --> 00:14:34,441
Ging: The real world tree
takes root in magma,

217
00:14:34,474 --> 00:14:36,776
grows out of a mountain,

218
00:14:36,810 --> 00:14:38,979
and is taller
than anything you’ve ever seen.

219
00:14:39,012 --> 00:14:43,283
As a matter of fact, it reaches
out of the atmosphere.

220
00:14:44,785 --> 00:14:48,289
in short,
it’s outside of this world.

221
00:14:49,356 --> 00:14:51,358
Gon: "Outside of this world"?

222
00:14:51,391 --> 00:14:52,959
Ging: At least outside

223
00:14:52,993 --> 00:14:54,962
the world map
you’re familiar with.

224
00:14:54,995 --> 00:14:57,331
( Gon gasps )

225
00:14:57,364 --> 00:14:59,299
♪

226
00:15:05,839 --> 00:15:08,308
Ging: The ants that you
and the chairman fought

227
00:15:08,342 --> 00:15:11,111
were a non-native species
from outside this world.

228
00:15:11,144 --> 00:15:14,414
that’s the truth
they don’t teach you in school.

229
00:15:16,183 --> 00:15:20,187
Adults know better than
to try to open pandora’s box,

230
00:15:20,220 --> 00:15:22,322
those with common sense, anyway.

231
00:15:25,859 --> 00:15:26,860
( Sighs )

232
00:15:31,431 --> 00:15:33,800
( Chuckles )

233
00:15:33,834 --> 00:15:36,804
guess if you
wanna put it another way,

234
00:15:36,837 --> 00:15:38,205
the world that we know

235
00:15:38,238 --> 00:15:42,542
is nothing but a small part
of a much bigger world.

236
00:15:46,013 --> 00:15:50,384
a chosen few,
from select times and places,

237
00:15:50,417 --> 00:15:53,287
left records of their travels
to the other side.

238
00:15:57,024 --> 00:15:58,058
Get it?

239
00:15:59,860 --> 00:16:03,430
The thing that I want
is always the same.

240
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:09,170
it’s always
something that I don’t have.

241
00:16:12,372 --> 00:16:13,573
( Gon chuckles )

242
00:16:27,321 --> 00:16:31,192
Ging: We need a lot of things
in order to get out there.

243
00:16:31,225 --> 00:16:34,395
Before you even begin,
there are four of ’em...

244
00:16:35,495 --> 00:16:38,064
The means, permission,

245
00:16:38,098 --> 00:16:42,002
qualifications, and a contract.

246
00:16:43,303 --> 00:16:45,005
Hate to say it,

247
00:16:45,038 --> 00:16:46,907
but I don’t have
any of those yet.

248
00:16:47,975 --> 00:16:50,077
Well, i’m not in any rush.

249
00:16:50,110 --> 00:16:53,246
I’m just enjoying the journey.

250
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:58,886
So if your chosen destination
is the same one as mine

251
00:16:58,919 --> 00:17:01,422
then enjoy the side trips...

252
00:17:02,923 --> 00:17:04,391
A lot, okay?

253
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:10,096
Things that are more important
than what you’re hunting for

254
00:17:10,130 --> 00:17:12,966
could be right there
by the side of the road.

255
00:17:15,435 --> 00:17:18,038
( Birds meowing )

256
00:17:22,576 --> 00:17:25,045
( Bird calls )

257
00:17:27,247 --> 00:17:29,282
( Squawks )

258
00:17:31,151 --> 00:17:33,053
( Meowing continues )

259
00:17:36,190 --> 00:17:37,124
( Gon gasps )

260
00:17:39,726 --> 00:17:40,694
Ging!

261
00:17:40,727 --> 00:17:41,928
Ging: Hmm?

262
00:17:41,962 --> 00:17:43,931
Gon: Here.

263
00:17:43,964 --> 00:17:45,666
Kite gave your license to me,

264
00:17:45,699 --> 00:17:48,302
and he said that I
should give it back to you.

